profile_positions.description:
(Yva.ai was acquired by Visier)
Development of three web apps.
Main responsibilities:
- Implementing business logic of applications;
- Development of architecture of the apps;
- Optimization of rendering to increase basic performance indicators;
- Resolving app’s security vulnerables;
- Code review and sharing the knowledge with the team.
Achievements:
- Updated code base from JS to TS;
- Implemented new state management using Redux Toolkit;
- Improved bundle size of apps and it's web vitals;
- Implemented new authorization and authentication ways.
Stack: TS, React, Redux-toolkit, Redux-observable, RxJS, React final form, Webpack, Styled components, Antd

Development of three web apps. Main responsibilities:
- Implementing business logic of applications;
- Development of architecture of the apps;
- Optimization of rendering to increase basic performance indicators; - Resolving app’s security vulnerables;
- Code review and sharing the knowledge with the team.
Achievements:
- Improved user experience and performance by changing Feed implementation to virtualized scroll;
- Reduced number of concurrent requests to server produced by rendered components to speed up the UI;
- Improved JS bundle size by reducing number of i18n files;
- Replaced old dashboard’s iframe routes with new designed pages to improve user experience.
Stack: JS/TS, React, Redux, RxJS, React final form, Webpack, Styled components, Antd, Material UI

Worked on a banking acquiring app. Responsibilities:
- Implementing business logic of application; - Rendering optimizations;
- CI/CD deployment;
- Covering application by unit tests;
- Microfrontend integrations.

Achievements:
- Implemented clean architecture design pattern in order to separate the business logic from view; - Switched forms logic to more optimized library and removed legacy code;
- Integrated with third party antivirus system;
- Optimized bundle size using webpack optimizations.
Stack: React, Mobx, Styled components, React final form, React-router, Jest, React-test-library.

As a full stack web developer:
Main responsibilities:
- Passing interviews to join the development team as part of an outstaff team (Yva.ai, was such a project);
- Start projects from scratch or integrate to already started projects;
- Evaluation of projects in terms of labor costs and complexity of implementation;
- Implementing the business logic of applications;
- Lead the development team;
- Code review.
Achievements:
- Implemented architecture for frontend and backend applications;
- Successfully integrated to different development processes;
- Developed microfrontend applications and integrated it to host apps;
- Developed internal HR system to track developer's activity and status;
- Developed api and backend business logic for testing tracking system, used internally.
Stack: JS/TS, Flow, React, Redux, Mobx, RxJS, React final form, Formik, React router, router5, Webpack 5, Lerna, Node.js, NestJS, ExpressJS, Strapi, JWT, PostgreSQL, SQLite, Typeorm, Docker.
As a Head of frontend department:
Main responsibilities:
- Lead the frontend department in Saint Petersburg's office;
- Conducting interviews with candidates for the position of front-end developer and hiring the best ones;
- Mentoring the newcomers;
- Making everyone pleased with their job.
Achievements:
- Successfully hired 10+ developers;
- Mentored 5+ developers. I am proud of these guys.

Developed a platform for freelancers in Australia.
Main responsibilities:
- Lead the team up to 6 developers;
- Implement the business logic of application (frontend and backend); - Integrate third party api's;
- Code review;
- Make decisions of project improvements along with the product owner.

Achievements:
- Lead the project to production stage of development;
- Implemented React hooks based functional components;
- Improved performance of web application using code splitting;
- Implemented core application logic both on backend and frontend sides; - Successfully extend app's functionality for video makers and designers
Stack: JS/TS, React, Redux, React-router, Sass, NodeJS, FeathersJS, PostgreSQL, Sequelize, third parties like TinyMCE, Keen, Xero, etc.
